abstract: Daily Mail says it has bought website Elite Daily, deal that is valued at somewhere between $40 and $50 million.
lead_paragraph: The British tabloid paid a reported $40 million to $50 million for Elite Daily, which specializes in articles and videos intended to be shared online.
